What Are the Key Drivers of the Global HVO and SAF Market?
1. Stringent Environmental Regulations
Governments worldwide continue strengthening emissions reduction policies to support climate goals and energy transition initiatives.

Programs such as the European Union's Renewable Energy Directive (RED III), ReFuelEU Aviation, FuelEU Maritime, the U.S. Renewable Fuel Standard (RFS), and various national blending mandates are significantly accelerating demand for renewable diesel and sustainable aviation fuels.

These regulations are encouraging fuel producers, airlines, and transportation companies to invest heavily in HVO and SAF adoption.

2. Growing Corporate Sustainability Commitments
Major airlines, logistics providers, shipping companies, and multinational corporations continue pursuing ambitious net-zero emission targets.

Long-term sustainable aviation fuel purchase agreements, renewable diesel adoption across commercial fleets, and ESG-driven procurement strategies are creating stable demand for HVO and SAF worldwide.

Corporate investments in low-carbon transportation continue strengthening long-term market growth.

3. Technological Advancements Improving Cost Competitiveness
Continuous innovation in hydroprocessing technologies, catalyst development, feedstock preprocessing, and refinery co-processing has significantly improved renewable fuel production efficiency.

These advancements have reduced production costs, expanded feedstock options, increased conversion efficiencies above 90%, and enhanced the commercial viability of HVO and SAF production.

